	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm curious as to what else your wizard would wear in the hand slot that is better than these. They are second best hand item for wizards as far as I can see.<br><br>You may well be at max INT, but items with lots of INT on them (and as far as I know, no gloves have more than 10) allow you to swap out one or two lower items for +mana/AC/resists/whatever.<br><br>A few extra saves are always handy, even though they are pretty low there are few hand items that give much in the way of saves at all, let alone a little to every save.<br><br>There is one item that I know of that has more than 35 mana in a hand slot - Shiny Metallic Gloves (AC10, INT9, MANA50, SVC/SVF8). It's be a toss-up as to whether you wanted the extra AC, mana and SVC/SVF vs the other saves and additional stats (STA/AGI/HP). Personally, I'd probably go for the shiny, but I'm unlikely to ever see either of them. :)<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
